-- Bentley Sales in China May More Than Double to 1,000 Cars, Daily Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-02T23:23:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/bentley-sales-in-china-may-more-than-double-to-1-000-cars-daily-reports.html
Bentley Motors Ltd.’s sales in China
this year may more than double from 2009, the China Daily
reported today, citing Zheng Biao, director of the company’s
China division.  The company may sell 1,000 cars in China this year after
having sold 421 in 2009, the newspaper reported. Bentley has 11
dealerships in China, with most of its cars priced at 4 million
yuan ($599,000) to 5 million yuan each, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  